Healthcare Dashboard Insight
The healthcare dashboard reveals several notable patterns across patient trends,
conditions, and demographics. Patient volume remains relatively stable throughout most years,
generally fluctuating between 850 and 1000 monthly, indicating consistent demand for healthcare services.
However, a sharp drop appears in May 2024, which may suggest incomplete data or an unusual external disruption.
Medical conditions such as obesity, hypertension, and diabetes consistently rank among the most common,
with a gradual increase from 2019 to 2023 before declining in 2024,
possibly reflecting improved interventions or reporting gaps.
The average patient age of 52 and an average admission duration of 15.5 days
suggest a middle-aged population requiring moderate-term care. Gender distribution is perfectly balanced,
highlighting equal service utilization. Test results are evenly split among normal, abnormal, and inconclusive,
which may indicate diagnostic complexity. Insurance coverage is also diversified, reducing dependency on a single provider.
Overall, the system appears stable but may benefit from deeper investigation into anomalies and condition trends.
